From 1e43b40914d62111fdff725dc8b729a2a0fd2182 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 5 Jul 2025 15:29:33 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] wifi:cfg80211: Add modparam for dfs testmode in cfg80211

On a 5 GHz AP operating on DFS channel 100 in 80 MHz bandwidth,
the AP interface goes down when radar is injected if dfs_test_mode
is enabled.

The hostapd brings down the AP interface as the kernel returns an
error during NL80211_CMD_UPDATE_AP.

The issue is observed on QSDK as part of the package upgrade.
In _cfg80211_reg_can_beacon, when the chandef to be checked is the
same one marked as radar, cfg80211_chandef_dfs_required returns a value
greater than zero. check_radar is assigned to true and
_cfg80211_chandef_usable is called with IEEE80211_CHAN_RADAR, and
it returns false. This causes _cfg80211_reg_can_beacon also to return
false. Consequently, the nl80211_update_ap returns EINVAL, and the
hostapd brings down the AP.

To fix this issue, add a module param "enable_dfs_test_mode"
in cfg80211. In _cfg80211_reg_can_beacon, if enable_dfs_test_mode
is set to true, mark check_radar as false.

Execute the following command to set the module param
"enable_dfs_test_mode" in cfg80211:

echo 1 > /sys/module/cfg80211/parameters/enable_dfs_test_mode

Tag: DFS
Patch-dependency: none

Signed-off-by: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/wireless/chan.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/wireless/chan.c b/net/wireless/chan.c
index 9a57eb4..e65b84e 100644
--- a/net/wireless/chan.c
+++ b/net/wireless/chan.c
@@ -21,6 +21,10 @@
 #define DISABLED_SUB_CHAN(freq, start_freq, punctured) \
  ((1 << (freq - start_freq)/MHZ_TO_KHZ(20)) & punctured)
 
+static bool enable_dfs_test_mode;
+module_param(enable_dfs_test_mode, bool, 0644);
+MODULE_PARM_DESC(enable_dfs_test_mode, "Enable DFS Test mode");
+
 static bool cfg80211_valid_60g_freq(u32 freq)
 {
 	return freq >= 58320 && freq <= 70200;
@@ -2087,6 +2091,9 @@ static bool _cfg80211_reg_can_beacon(struct wiphy *wiphy,
 		check_radar = false;
 	}
 
+	if (enable_dfs_test_mode)
+		check_radar = false;
+
 	if (check_radar &&
 	    !_cfg80211_chandef_usable(wiphy, chandef,
 				      IEEE80211_CHAN_RADAR, 0))
-- 
2.34.1

